-- U.K.'s Cavendish Wins 123-Mile Tour de France Stage With Breakaway Sprint
-- Chris Elser
-- 2010-07-23T15:44:12Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-23/contador-maintains-tour-de-france-lead-cavendish-wins-123-mile-18th-stage.html

          
          
             Mark Cavendish won the 123-mile 18th
stage of the Tour de France by sprinting away from the main
group at the end of today’s race.  
 The victory was the fourth time Britain’s Cavendish has won
a stage in this year’s event. Today’s race went from Salies-de-
Bearn to Bordeaux. Alberto Contador kept his place at the top of
the leader board.  
          
          


  


        